  "prompt": "How do I deal with extreme confusion, pain & helplessness after being completely cut off by my S.O, who doesn't want any type of contact ever?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're going through this difficult experience. Dealing with extreme confusion, pain, and helplessness after being cut off by a significant other is incredibly challenging. Here are some steps you can take to help manage your emotions and begin to heal:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Pain**: It's important to recognize and accept your feelings. Allow yourself to feel the hurt, confusion, and helplessness. Bottling up emotions can lead to further distress.\n\n2. **Reach Out for Support**: Share your feelings with trusted friends, family members, or a therapist. Talking to someone who understands can provide comfort and perspective. Professional counseling can be particularly helpful in navigating these complex emotions.\n\n3. **Take Care of Yourself**: Focus on self-care. Engage in activities that you enjoy and that help you relax. Exercise, healthy eating, and sufficient sleep can improve your overall well-being.\n\n4. **Establish Routine and Stability**: Creating a daily routine can provide structure and help you feel more in control. Even when you're struggling, having consistent activities can offer a sense of normalcy.\n\n5. **Avoid Unproductive Patterns**:\n   - **Limit Social Media**: Minimize the temptation to check your S.O.\u2019s social media profiles, as this often exacerbates feelings of pain and confusion.\n   - **Avoid Substance Abuse**: Resist the urge to cope through alcohol or drugs, as this will only provide temporary relief and can worsen the situation.\n\n6. **Set Boundaries**: Respect their wish for no contact. Pushing for communication can lead to more hurt and hinder your healing process.\n\n7. **Reflect and Learn**: With time, try to reflect on the relationship and understand what you can learn from the experience. This doesn't mean blaming yourself but rather gaining insights that can help you grow.\n\n8. **Explore New Interests**: Open yourself to new hobbies or interests. Engaging in activities you're passionate about can be fulfilling and divert your mind from the pain.\n\n9. **Give Yourself Time**: Healing from such a deep emotional wound takes time. Be patient with yourself and understand that it's a gradual process.\n\n10. **Consider Professional Help**: If your feelings of confusion, pain, and helplessness are overwhelming and persistent, consider seeking professional help. Therapy can provide tools and strategies to manage your emotions effectively.\n\nLastly, remember that your feelings are valid and it's okay to seek help and support when you need it. Healing is possible, and with time and self-care, you'll be able to navigate this challenging period.",
